05/01/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in the south-eastern town of Gjirokastra seized 190kg of hashish in two separate operations at the weekend.
Police arrested three people with almost 100kg of hashish in a bar in Gjirokastra on Sunday (January 4th).
They seized another 90kg in the nearby village of Pepel.
Police sources said neighbouring Greece was the drugs' intended destination.
(Top Channel, Telegrafi, Ora News - 04/01/09)
